{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rendering Arrays with map()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The standard way to render a list of items in React is to transform a data array into an array of JSX elements using "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Array.map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". React accepts an array of JSX elements anywhere it accepts a single element — in the return block, inside "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " within JSX, or as children of a container element."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Diagram showing data array (three user objects) flowing through Array.map() in a component to produce three <li> DOM elements",
          "title": "Array.map() — Data to JSX Elements"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Basic Pattern"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Call "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on the array inside "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in JSX. The callback returns a JSX element for each item. Every element in the list must have a unique "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " prop:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function UserList({ users }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {users.map(user => (\n        <li key={user.id}>\n          {user.name}\n        </li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " prop is not rendered to the DOM — it is used internally by React to track which elements changed between renders. Without keys, React falls back to index-based tracking, which causes incorrect behaviour when items are reordered, added, or removed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why map() Works in JSX"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX expressions accept any value that React knows how to render. React renders arrays of elements by walking the array and inserting each element into the output in order. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " returns an array of JSX elements — exactly what React needs:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// What you write\n{users.map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)}\n\n// What JS evaluates to (an array of elements)\n[\n  <li key=\"1\">Alice</li>,\n  <li key=\"2\">Bob</li>,\n  <li key=\"3\">Carol</li>,\n]\n\n// React renders each element in sequence:\n// <li>Alice</li>\n// <li>Bob</li>\n// <li>Carol</li>"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "React also renders "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "null",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "undefined",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "false",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside arrays as nothing — useful when some items should be conditionally excluded:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Items with no name are skipped\n{users.map(u =>\n  u.name ? <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li> : null\n)}\n\n// Or filter first, then map — cleaner\n{users\n  .filter(u => u.name)\n  .map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rendering Component Lists"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In practice, each list item is often a custom component rather than a primitive element. Pass the item data as props and put "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on the outermost element returned by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function ProductGrid({ products }) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"grid\">\n      {products.map(product => (\n        // key goes on the outermost element — here the ProductCard\n        <ProductCard\n          key={product.id}\n          name={product.name}\n          price={product.price}\n          imageUrl={product.imageUrl}\n          onAddToCart={() => addToCart(product.id)}\n        />\n      ))}\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " prop is not passed through to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ProductCard",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — it is consumed by React before the component sees its props. If you need the ID inside the component, pass it as a separate prop ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "id={product.id}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ")."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Returning Multiple Elements from map()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When each item should render as more than one adjacent element, wrap them in a fragment and place "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on the fragment. Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fragment",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " explicitly here — the short "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "<>",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " syntax does not accept attributes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { Fragment } from 'react';\n\nfunction DefinitionList({ terms }) {\n  return (\n    <dl>\n      {terms.map(term => (\n        // Fragment with key — allows dt + dd pair per item\n        <Fragment key={term.id}>\n          <dt>{term.word}</dt>\n          <dd>{term.definition}</dd>\n        </Fragment>\n      ))}\n    </dl>\n  );\n}\n\n// Short syntax — NOT valid when you need a key\n// This will cause a warning:\n{terms.map(term => (\n  <>\n    <dt>{term.word}</dt>\n    <dd>{term.definition}</dd>\n  </>\n))}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nested map() Calls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nested data requires nested "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " calls. Each level of nesting needs its own "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " that is unique within that level:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function CategoryList({ categories }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {categories.map(category => (\n        <li key={category.id}>\n          <h3>{category.name}</h3>\n          <ul>\n            {category.items.map(item => (\n              // key only needs to be unique within THIS ul\n              <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>\n            ))}\n          </ul>\n        </li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keys only need to be unique among siblings in the same array — not globally unique across the whole component. An item with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "id: 5",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in category A and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "id: 5",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in category B are fine because they live in separate arrays."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Extracting List Items to a Separate Component"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " callback grows large, extract it to a named component. This improves readability and makes each list item independently testable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// ❌ Verbose inline callback\nfunction OrderList({ orders }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {orders.map(order => (\n        <li key={order.id}>\n          <span className={order.status}>{order.status}</span>\n          <strong>{order.total}</strong>\n          <small>{order.date}</small>\n          <button onClick={() => cancel(order.id)}>Cancel</button>\n        </li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}\n\n// ✓ Extracted component — cleaner map(), item is testable independently\nfunction OrderRow({ order, onCancel }) {\n  return (\n    <li>\n      <span className={order.status}>{order.status}</span>\n      <strong>{order.total}</strong>\n      <small>{order.date}</small>\n      <button onClick={() => onCancel(order.id)}>Cancel</button>\n    </li>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction OrderList({ orders, onCancel }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {orders.map(order => (\n        <OrderRow key={order.id} order={order} onCancel={onCancel} />\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inline vs Extracted map() Function"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " call can be placed inline in JSX or hoisted into a variable before the return statement. Both are valid — choose based on readability:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Inline — fine for short callbacks\nfunction TagList({ tags }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {tags.map(tag => <span key={tag} className=\"tag\">{tag}</span>)}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// Hoisted variable — better when pre-processing is needed\nfunction TagList({ tags }) {\n  const tagElements = tags\n    .filter(tag => tag.length > 0)\n    .sort()\n    .map(tag => <span key={tag} className=\"tag\">{tag}</span>);\n\n  return <div>{tagElements}</div>;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Passing Index from map()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " passes the current index as the second argument to the callback. The index is useful for display purposes (row numbers, alternating styles) but should not be used as the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " unless the list is static and never reordered:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function NumberedList({ items }) {\n  return (\n    <ol>\n      {items.map((item, index) => (\n        <li\n          key={item.id}                    // ✓ stable ID as key\n          className={index % 2 === 0 ? 'even' : 'odd'}  // ✓ index for stripe\n        >\n          {index + 1}. {item.label}       {/* ✓ index for display number */}\n        </li>\n      ))}\n    </ol>\n  );\n}\n\n// ❌ Index as key — causes incorrect behaviour on reorder or insert\n{items.map((item, index) => (\n  <li key={index}>{item.label}</li>\n))}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Mistake"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "What goes wrong"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Fix"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "No key prop"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "React warns; incorrect reconciliation on update"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Add unique key from data (id, slug)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Using index as key"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Wrong item receives state/focus on reorder"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use stable data ID; index only for static lists"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Key on inner element"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "React warns; missing the outer sibling key"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Put key on the outermost element returned by map()"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "forEach instead of map"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "forEach returns undefined; nothing renders"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use .map() which returns an array"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Empty Array Handling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the array is empty, "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".map()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " returns an empty array and React renders nothing. Always decide what to show when the list is empty:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function TaskList({ tasks }) {\n  if (tasks.length === 0) {\n    return <p className=\"empty\">No tasks yet. Add one above.</p>;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {tasks.map(task => (\n        <li key={task.id}>{task.title}</li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}\n\n// Alternative inline\nfunction TaskList({ tasks }) {\n  return tasks.length > 0\n    ? <ul>{tasks.map(t => <li key={t.id}>{t.title}</li>)}</ul>\n    : <p>No tasks yet.</p>;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Rendered Lists"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { render, screen, within } from '@testing-library/react';\n\nconst users = [\n  { id: 1, name: 'Alice' },\n  { id: 2, name: 'Bob' },\n];\n\ntest('renders one list item per user', () => {\n  render(<UserList users={users} />);\n  const items = screen.getAllByRole('listitem');\n  expect(items).toHaveLength(2);\n});\n\ntest('renders each user name', () => {\n  render(<UserList users={users} />);\n  expect(screen.getByText('Alice')).toBeInTheDocument();\n  expect(screen.getByText('Bob')).toBeInTheDocument();\n});\n\ntest('renders empty state when no users', () => {\n  render(<UserList users={[]} />);\n  expect(screen.queryAllByRole('listitem')).toHaveLength(0);\n  expect(screen.getByText(/no tasks yet/i)).toBeInTheDocument();\n});"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Combining map() with filter() and sort()" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Array methods chain cleanly before " },
          { "type": "text", "text": ".map()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": ". Filter before you map to skip items; sort before you map to control display order. Never mutate the original array inside a render — use " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "[...array].sort()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " to sort a copy:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "function ActiveUserList({ users, searchQuery, sortBy }) {\n  const listItems = users\n    .filter(u => u.isActive)                          // 1. remove inactive\n    .filter(u =>\n      !searchQuery ||\n      u.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchQuery.toLowerCase())\n    )                                                  // 2. apply search\n    .sort((a, b) => {                                  // 3. sort (copy implied by spread)\n      if (sortBy === 'name') return a.name.localeCompare(b.name);\n      if (sortBy === 'date') return new Date(b.createdAt) - new Date(a.createdAt);\n      return 0;\n    })\n    .map(u => <UserRow key={u.id} user={u} />);       // 4. render\n\n  return listItems.length > 0\n    ? <ul>{listItems}</ul>\n    : <EmptyState query={searchQuery} />;\n}" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "The " },
          { "type": "text", "text": ".sort()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " call sorts the already-filtered array in place. Since " },
          { "type": "text", "text": ".filter()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " returns a new array, you are not mutating the original " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "users", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " prop." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Rendering Maps, Sets, and Other Iterables" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "React's " },
          { "type": "text", "text": ".map()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " pattern requires an array. If your data is a " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "Map", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": ", " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "Set", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": ", or other iterable, convert it first:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "// Map<id, user> → render as list\nfunction UserMap({ userMap }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {[...userMap.entries()].map(([id, user]) => (\n        <li key={id}>{user.name}</li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}\n\n// Set<string> → unique tags\nfunction TagCloud({ tagSet }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {[...tagSet].map(tag => (\n        <span key={tag} className=\"tag\">{tag}</span>\n      ))}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// Object entries → key-value pairs\nfunction ConfigList({ config }) {\n  return (\n    <dl>\n      {Object.entries(config).map(([key, value]) => (\n        <Fragment key={key}>\n          <dt>{key}</dt>\n          <dd>{String(value)}</dd>\n        </Fragment>\n      ))}\n    </dl>\n  );\n}" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Performance: Avoid Creating Functions Inside map()" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Each render call to " },
          { "type": "text", "text": ".map()", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " creates a new function for every event handler defined inline. For short lists this is negligible, but for very long lists or frequently re-rendering components, prefer stable callbacks:" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "jsx" },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "// ⚠ New function created per item per render (usually fine)\nfunction TodoList({ todos, onDelete }) {\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {todos.map(todo => (\n        <li key={todo.id}>\n          {todo.title}\n          <button onClick={() => onDelete(todo.id)}>Delete</button>\n        </li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}\n\n// ✓ Stable reference — memoised item component absorbs the click\nconst TodoItem = React.memo(function TodoItem({ todo, onDelete }) {\n  return (\n    <li>\n      {todo.title}\n      <button onClick={() => onDelete(todo.id)}>Delete</button>\n    </li>\n  );\n});\n\nfunction TodoList({ todos, onDelete }) {\n  // onDelete should be stable (useCallback at the parent)\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {todos.map(todo => (\n        <TodoItem key={todo.id} todo={todo} onDelete={onDelete} />\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  );\n}" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "Profile before optimising. The inline arrow function pattern is idiomatic React and appropriate for most lists. Only reach for " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "React.memo", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " and " },
          { "type": "text", "text": "useCallback", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }] },
          { "type": "text", "text": " when the profiler shows a measurable problem." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
